        "text": "The AI agent infrastructure story of mid-2026 is a paradox: MCP has achieved remarkable protocol-layer standardization in record time (97M monthly downloads, 10K+ servers, all major platforms), while the operational layer — security, governance, production deployment — is dangerously immature. The defining crisis: 78-89% of enterprises have agent pilots, but fewer than 15% have moved anything to production at scale.",
